---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About - SalaryCalculator.sg" description="Learn about SalaryCalculator.sg, the free Singapore salary calculator built by Mottalib Radif. Understand how we calculate CPF contributions and income tax.">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://salarycalculator.sg/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "About", "item": "https://salarycalculator.sg/about/" }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">/</span>
      <span class="text-gray-800">About</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About SalaryCalculator.sg</h1>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Who Built This Calculator</h2>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-5 mb-4">
        <img src="/team/mottalib-radif.jpg" alt="Mottalib Radif" class="h-20 w-20 rounded-full object-cover border-4 border-white shadow-lg flex-shrink-0" width="80" height="80" loading="eager" />
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">Mottalib Radif</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-medium">MBA, INSEAD &middot; Singapore Personal Finance Enthusiast</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        SalaryCalculator.sg was created by <strong>Mottalib Radif</strong>, an MBA graduate from INSEAD, one of the world's leading business schools. Passionate about Singapore personal finance, Mottalib combines his expertise in financial technology with a thorough understanding of the Singapore tax system — CPF contributions, IRAS income tax brackets, and employee reliefs — to build accurate, transparent, and easy-to-use calculators for every worker in Singapore.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Our Mission</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The mission of SalaryCalculator.sg is to provide Singapore employees, job seekers, and HR professionals with a fast, free, and accurate tool for calculating take-home pay. Understanding your net salary after CPF contributions and income tax can be complicated, especially for Permanent Residents with graduated CPF rates or foreigners navigating Singapore's tax system for the first time. Our goal is to simplify this process and help every worker in Singapore understand exactly what they will receive in their bank account.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">How the Calculator Works</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Our calculator applies the current CPF contribution rates based on your residency status (Singapore Citizen, Permanent Resident by year, or Foreigner) and age group. It computes the employee and employer CPF contributions, respecting the Ordinary Wage (OW) ceiling and Additional Wage (AW) ceiling. It then calculates your Singapore income tax using the progressive tax brackets published by the Inland Revenue Authority of Singapore (IRAS), taking into account applicable personal reliefs such as Earned Income Relief and CPF Relief.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The result is a comprehensive breakdown of your gross salary, CPF contributions split across the Ordinary Account (OA), Special Account (SA), and Medisave Account (MA), income tax payable, and your final take-home pay. All calculations are performed entirely in your browser, so your salary information is never transmitted to any server or stored anywhere.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Data Sources</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        All CPF contribution rates, allocation ratios, and wage ceilings are sourced directly from the Central Provident Fund Board (cpf.gov.sg). Income tax rates, brackets, and relief amounts come from the Inland Revenue Authority of Singapore (iras.gov.sg). We update our calculator whenever these agencies publish new rates or policy changes, typically at the start of each calendar year or when mid-year adjustments are announced.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This calculator provides estimates for general informational purposes only. It does not account for every possible tax relief, rebate, or special circumstance. Your actual take-home pay may differ based on additional deductions, employer benefits, or specific tax situations. We recommend consulting IRAS or a qualified tax professional for precise calculations related to your individual circumstances.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        We welcome your feedback, questions, and suggestions for improvement. If you spot any inaccuracies or have ideas for new features, please reach out through our website. We are committed to maintaining the most accurate and helpful salary calculator for Singapore.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
